    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "We should ever remember that in the judgment we must meet the record of the way we use God&apos;s money. Much is spent in self-pleasing, self-gratification, that does us no real good, but positive injury. If we realize that God is the giver of all good things, that the money is His, then we shall exercise wisdom in its expenditure, conforming to His holy will. The world, its customs, its fashions, will not be our standard. We shall not have a desire to conform to its practices; we shall not permit our own inclinations to control us.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">4<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"Lt 8, 1889\" data-link=\"14056.4339001\">Letter 8, 1889</span>.</span></a></sup>",
