    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 368.4 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "<strong>Systematic Giving for the Family</strong>&mdash;&ldquo;Let every one of you lay by him in store, as God hath prospered him.&rdquo; Every member of the family, from the oldest down to the youngest, may take part in this work of benevolence.... The plan of systematic benevolence [<span class=\"non-egw-note\">Note: Reference is here made to plans followed early by the church in laying aside weekly the tithes and offerings.&mdash;<em>Compilers</em>.</span>] will prove a safeguard to every family against temptations to spend <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"369\"></span> means for needless things, and especially will it prove a blessing to the rich by guarding them from indulging in extravagances.",
    "puborder": 1122,
