    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "The squandering of money in luxuries deprives the poor of the means necessary to supply them with food and clothing. That which is spent for the gratification of pride in dress, in buildings, in furniture, and in decorations would relieve the distress of many wretched, suffering families. God&apos;s stewards are to minister to the needy.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">10<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"RH 12-8-1896\" data-link=\"821.15486\">The Review and Herald, December 8, 1896</span>.</span></a></sup>",
